            <div class="additional-content">
                <h2><a name="cite"></a>Share and Cite</h2>

                <div class="social-media-links" style="text-align: left;">
                    <a href="mailto:?&amp;subject=From%20MDPI%3A%20%22Mathematical%20Proposal%20for%20Securing%20Split%20Learning%20Using%20Homomorphic%20Encryption%20and%20Zero-Knowledge%20Proofs&quot;&amp;body=https://www.mdpi.com/3215706%3A%0A%0AMathematical%20Proposal%20for%20Securing%20Split%20Learning%20Using%20Homomorphic%20Encryption%20and%20Zero-Knowledge%20Proofs%0A%0AAbstract%3A%20This%20work%20presents%20a%20mathematical%20solution%20to%20data%20privacy%20and%20integrity%20issues%20in%20Split%20Learning%20which%20uses%20Homomorphic%20Encryption%20%28HE%29%20and%20Zero-Knowledge%20Proofs%20%28ZKP%29.%20It%20allows%20calculations%20to%20be%20conducted%20on%20encrypted%20data%2C%20keeping%20the%20data%20private%2C%20while%20ZKP%20ensures%20the%20correctness%20of%20these%20calculations%20without%20revealing%20the%20underlying%20data.%20Our%20proposed%20system%2C%20HavenSL%2C%20combines%20HE%20and%20ZKP%20to%20provide%20strong%20protection%20against%20attacks.%20It%20uses%20Discrete%20Cosine%20Transform%20%28DCT%29%20to%20analyze%20model%20updates%20in%20the%20frequency%20domain%20to%20detect%20unusual%20changes%20in%20parameters.%20HavenSL%20also%20has%20a%20rollback%20feature%20that%20brings%20the%20system%20back%20to%20a%20verified%20state%20if%20harmful%20changes%20are%20detected.%20Experiments%20on%20CIFAR-10%2C%20MNIST%2C%20and%20Fashion-MNIST%20datasets%20show%20that%20using%20Homomorphic%20Encryption%20and%20Zero-Knowledge%20Proofs%20during%20training%20is%20feasible%20and%20accuracy%20is%20maintained.%20This%20mathematical-based%20approach%20shows%20how%20crypto-graphic%20can%20protect%20decentralized%20learning%20systems.%20It%20also%20proves%20the%20practical%20use%20of%20HE%20and%20ZKP%20in%20secure%2C%20privacy-aware%20collaborative%20AI." title="Email">
                        <i class="fa fa-envelope-square" style="font-size: 30px;"></i>
                    </a>

